'''''Quest 1''''' is a single-player [[Role-playing video game|role-playing game]] originally written for the [[TRS-80]] and translated for the [[Apple II]] and [[Atari 8-bit computers]]. Published by ''[[SoftSide|SoftSide Magazine]]'' in 1981 as a [[type-in program]],<ref name="Softwide">{{cite magazine |last=Reynolds |first=Brian |date=August 1981 |title=Quest 1 |magazine=Softside Magazine |location=Milford, NH |publisher=Roger Robitaille Sr.}}</ref><ref name="Internet Archive">{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/details/softside-magazine-35/mode/2up |title=Softside Magazine 35 |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=August 1981 |website=archive.org |publisher=Internet Archive |access-date=October 10, 2020}}</ref> it is the first-known published game by [[Brian Reynolds (game designer)|Brian Reynolds]]. ''Quest 1'' was republished in ''The Best of SoftSide'' (1983) and released on accompanying [[floppy disk|5Â¼-inch floppy disks]].<ref name="bss">{{cite book|editor=Fred Condo|title=The Best of SoftSide|year=1983|publisher=SoftSide Publications, Inc.|location=Milford, New Hampshire|chapter=Quest}}</ref>

